# clangd language-server configuration. Pairs with the compile_commands.json
# that CMake generates (CMakePresets.json sets CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON
# for both `dev-debug` and `dev-release` presets). clangd reads per-file
# compile flags from there, so VIXL-derived sources automatically get the
# relaxed warnings configured by gaby_vm_apply_imported_compile_flags() and
# project-authored sources stay strict (-Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic) — the
# editor-side warning experience matches the build-side policy.
#
# Pointing at build/debug rather than build/release because the debug build
# defines VIXL_DEBUG, which keeps assertion paths and debug-only branches
# alive in the AST clangd parses — better navigation, more accurate
# find-references. Switch to build/release if you want a leaner parse.
#
# Run `cmake --preset dev-debug` once after cloning so build/debug exists
# and compile_commands.json is generated; clangd picks it up automatically.

CompileFlags:
  CompilationDatabase: build/debug
